data.enText: a period of time that is spent doing a particular activity

data.chText: 一次摄影，一场录音，一堂训练课等
这门课总共上12次，每次两小时。
data.enText: The course is made up of 12 two-hour sessions.

data.chText: （法庭的）开庭，开庭期；（议会等的）会议，会期
data.enText: a formal meeting or series of meetings of a court, a parliament, etc.; a period of time when such meetings are held
a session of the UN General Assembly
The court is now in session .

data.chText: 委员会举行了秘密会议。
data.enText: The committee met in closed session (= with nobody else present) .

data.chText: （酒吧中）演奏会（尤指演奏爱尔兰音乐）
data.enText: an occasion when people meet to play music, especially Irish music, in a pub/bar

word_means: 为录音的歌手或乐队伴奏的

means: （酒吧中）演奏会（尤指演奏爱尔兰音乐）
为录音的歌手或乐队伴奏的

ex.enText: The meeting will be held next week.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指人们集合在一起讨论或决定某事的集会，可用于任何场合。

ex.chText: 世界和平大会将在日内瓦举行。
ex.enText: The International Peace Conference will be held in Geneva.

ex.chText: 多名代表出席了联合国环境大会。
ex.enText: More than 100 representatives attended the UN conference on the environment. 100

synonyms.bx: 尤指会持续数天的、有关政治、商业等重要事务的大型正式会议。

ex.chText: 今年的教师大会即将召开。
ex.enText: This year's teacher's convention is around the corner.

ex.chText: 他们在哪里召开党员大会？
ex.enText: Where are they holding their party convention?

synonyms.bx: 指同一职业、同一组织或有共同爱好的人聚在一起召开的大型正式会议。

ex.chText: 电视直播的议会会议什么时候开始？
ex.enText: When will the televised session of parliament start?

ex.chText: 委员会成员为什么举行闭门会议？
ex.enText: Why did the board members meet in closed session?

synonyms.bx: 指正式会议，尤指议会的一次会议或系列会议。

tr: a meeting devoted to a particular activity
a meeting for execution of a group's functions
example: it was the opening session of the legislature
the seance was held in the medium's parlor

tr: the time during which a school holds classes
example: they had to shorten the school term

value.def: A session is a meeting of a court, parliament, or other official group.

example.ex: After two late night sessions, the Security Council has failed to reach agreement...
example.tran: 在深夜召开两次会议后，安全理事会还是没有达成一致。

value.def: A session is a period during which the meetings of a court, parliament, or other official group are regularly held.

example.ex: The parliamentary session ends on October 4th...
From September until December, Congress remained in session.
example.tran: 从 9 月到 12 月，国会一直都在开会。

value.tran: (议会等的)会期;(法庭的)开庭期

value.def: A session of a particular activity is a period of that activity.

example.ex: The two leaders emerged for a photo session.
example.tran: 两位领导现身接受记者拍照。

value.tran: (某项活动的)一段时间，一场，一节

value.def: Session musicians are employed to play backing music in recording studios.

example.ex: He established himself as a session musician.
example.tran: 他成为了一位伴奏音乐家。

trans: (乐队为录音而雇用的)临时乐师
